       [1m-f     [22mdmenu grabs the keyboard before reading stdin if not reading from a tty. This is faster, but will lock up X until stdin reaches end-of-file.

       [1m-i     [22mdmenu matches menu items case insensitively.

       [1m-l [4m[22mlines[0m
